rComments: Il semble connaître sa matière, mais ne devrait pas l'enseigner en français puisqu'il ne peut pas l'expliquer. Il ne devrait pas enseigner en français. Les évaluations sont très subjectives. Les cours sont d'environ une heure et non 2h50. Il est difficile à contacter et n'est pas là pour ses étudiants. Il ne semble pas aimer enseigner.

This is the second time I've had Kyle as a professor. I think he's great, but he never responds to e-mails. There were 2 quizzes, a written outline, a midpoint assessment, a final reflection, and 9 weekly reflections on a Performance and Wellness Plan. He is very fair with his grading, but the quizzes were tough. There also was a lot of reading.

This prof is what every prof should be. His lectures are amazing and he has no exams. But you do have to be in class for the weekly quizzes. This prof required mind maps for each weeks theme which are very time consuming but if you work hard are fun to do. There is also a paper as a final.

I absolutely loved Kyle's lectures. He kept every lecture interesting and was such a personable professor and I really appreciated his testing us with mind maps and in class video content rather than exams. He opened me up to a whole new discipline in sport that I have now decided to get my masters degree in. Would 100% recommend him to anyone.

Weekly quizzes make the class mandatory but are relatively easy, and the textbook is required. 3 major assignments but got good marks on them (A+, A, B) and no exam or midterm. Gave bonus marks too. Annoying that class was mandatory due to quizzes and in class assignments but made it worth it not having an exam

Kyle's course was lowkey awful. He seemed to care a lot for us and knows what he's talking about. He was very unclear with his expectations and seemed to mark assignments harshly. When you submit take 15%-20% off what you think your work is worth and that will be your grade. Must read the textbook because he tests exact wording instead of concepts.

I liked that we had quizzes, links to make between the book and videos, mind maps and a chapter revision. However, I felt I had to put in a lot time in this class to keep up with all the readings and mind maps. I also felt that he wasn't very clear with what he wanted and didn't really give good feedback on why marks were taken off.

Cares about his students, is really knowledgable in his area of expertise. Gives you strategies for success outside of the classroom. You need to really engage in his lectures to get a good grade, it's not enough to memorize the slides.
